OL,7,FIt was soon after that Sudan
OL,8,Fdisappeared from the attention of the
OL,9,Fworld.
OL,11,FYet two years on today, while Sudan's
OL,12,Fcapital may no longer be burning as it
OL,13,Fonce did, it is an empty shell,
OL,14,Fhollowed out, destroyed and vacant of
OL,15,Fthe vibrant communities that made up
OL,16,Fwhat it once was. And crucially,
OL,17,FSudan's agony has got worse.
