OL,7,FHead of UNICEF Sudan, Sheldon Yett,
OL,8,Ftold us this figure represents the few
OL,9,Fcases that they managed to record,
OL,10,Fsaying the problem is far bigger: "We
OL,11,Fwere able to document some 220 cases
OL,12,Fof children being raped. And these are
OL,13,Fchildren in all parts of the country.
OL,15,F"These children are sometimes as young
OL,16,Fas one years old, boys and girls. We
OL,17,Fknow that this is just the tip of the
OL,18,Ficeberg. There are many, many more
OL,19,Fchildren and of course, no-one should
OL,20,Fhave to go through this."
